            </V>
            <V n="text" t="variation">
              <U n="variation">
                <L n="variations">
                  <T>0xC9E5FA35<!--My sister and her husband used to be dead like me; Tziporah resurrected herself with Ambrosia, and I've heard Radwan was Reborn at the Baleful Bog right here in our Mourningvale! --></T>
                  <T>0xFD1D2C58<!--I swear, the way the Reaper Career has spread around here makes you wonder if it's actually a career choice or something a little more, well, <i>consuming</i>. I'll admit it, though, the whole reason I bought into it was because it meant I had a chance to look at those amazing scry bowls. Like, are those an amazing aesthetic or what?--></T>
                  <T>0xC50FD7A9<!--The Ancestor is probably the most beautiful part of Whispering Glen in my opinion. Scholars and scientists here claim it was an effigy of a long dead ruler, though considering how long I've been dead, even I don't know who carved it. Some local "paranormal experts" say the tears that the visage cries during the full moon can link back to the Netherworld, some just say it's flood water run off. Did you know it's the place people perform old rituals during the full moon? Ah, <i>rituals</i>. Just thinking about them warms my heart.--></T>
                </L>
              </U>
            </V>
            <V n="title" t="enabled">
              <T n="enabled">0xEBB55930<!--Ravenwood Rumors--></T>
            </V>
            <E n="visual_type">SPEECH</E>
          </U>
        </V>
        <L n="tests">
          <L>
            <V t="relationship">
              <U n="relationship">
                <U n="relationship_score_interval">
                  <T n="upper_bound">32</T>
                </U>
