                  </L>
                </U>
              </V>
            </V>
            <V n="text" t="variation">
              <U n="variation">
                <L n="variations">
                  <T>0x8CBC22ED<!--Way back when I was still living, I wanted to know everything I could about the ghostly world. Now, of course, I'm literally a ghost so I suppose it seems as if I know all there is to know. I still really wanted to dabble in Ghost History, to feel like I'm truly the most knowledgeable ghostie I can be. Mainly because I can't stand the thought of Waylon lording that over me. Waylon! You're not in charge of <i>everything</i> around here! Chill out!--></T>
                  <T>0xACC9869<!--Oh! Have you met Lady Ravendancer yet? She's such an idol, I love her. We go way, way, way back. Modern mortals don't know much about her other than that she is a renowned spellcaster and tarot card reader. She once had a legion of followers named <i>The Order of Lenore</i> that has since dwindled over the years. She has ties to the Gomes family, did you know? Some of her followers still exist, I love watching them search for her tarot deck.--></T>
                </L>
              </U>
            </V>
            <V n="title" t="enabled">
              <T n="enabled">0xEBB55930<!--Ravenwood Rumors--></T>
            </V>
            <E n="visual_type">SPEECH</E>
          </U>
        </V>
        <L n="tests">
