                </U>
              </V>
            </V>
            <V n="text" t="variation">
              <U n="variation">
                <L n="variations">
                  <T>0xA0C6A234<!--Waylon and I are "old" friends, and by old I mean we've both been dead a very, very, <i>very</i> long time. We're close, but I know full well that he's a little excessive. Did you know he writes the script for the "Ravenwood Welcoming Committee" and anyone on it has to read it? The guy's just a wee bit, well, insufferable. --></T>
                  <T>0xC49EB861<!--Some Sims can be so cruel or uncaring. I've heard them tell stories about that poor, dear ghost by the Guardian Tree. Alice is her name, you know. She lost one of her children in an especially tragic way, but she's missing all of her children. But the way the stories spin it is all wrong! They talk about her like she's terrifying and unapproachable. I'm sure that if you just helped her by talking to her and seeing if there's anything that would help her be more at peace, they'd find a version of Alice that's rather changed from the "scary" ghost story Sims tell. --></T>
                  <T>0xAE3796A3<!--It's awkward being distant from a sibling you don't even dislike, but Tziporah and I just haven't gotten along for a while. I'm not sure if you realize this, but she was a ghost too for a long, long time before she decided to take ambrosia. It almost felt like a betrayal, given how long we were together. To make things worse, she wants me to take ambrosia now, too. Why? What's wrong with my life the way it is now?--></T>
                </L>
              </U>
            </V>
            <V n="title" t="enabled">
              <T n="enabled">0xEBB55930<!--Ravenwood Rumors--></T>
            </V>
